The paper presents new algorithms for adaptively learning artificial neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithms are specifically designed for neural networks, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical analysis and data-dependent generalization guarantees, which are topics that are often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve binary classification tasks extracted from the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is a popular dataset used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
